Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Loughnan Glossary
Author: LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page: 74
Edition:
Quote: snow fence: one which has been built in the full knowledge that it will be damaged by each winter's snow and so will need annual repair. But by then it has done its job for the year of confining sheep within the winter block.
